A vintage 1950s-style illustration of three anthropomorphic coffee beans wearing tiny lab coats, standing around a miniature chemistry set on a wooden workbench. Each bean has a distinct personality shown through posture and expression - one examining a test tube, one taking notes on a clipboard, one adjusting a microscope. The scene is bathed in warm sepia and cream tones with subtle coffee stain textures in the background. Scattered around them are tiny beakers filled with amber liquid, vintage brass measuring instruments, and delicate steam wisps rising from a porcelain cup nearby. The aesthetic evokes mid-century scientific advertisements with crosshatching details and muted earth tones of brown, tan, and sage green.
